  			</div>
  		</div><div>
  			<div id="item-2901"><p>Both of those look delicious, Leland, and I agree, five minutes per side would not have been enough cooking time for a two pound flank steak. Did you let your steak sit for awhile after cooking so the juices could settle and not run all over the platter when you sliced it?</p>
<p>One small quibble; I don&#8217;t think 15 minutes technically can be called <strong>blanching</strong>; by definition I believe blanching means a brief sojourn in boiling water. I think 15 minutes is plain old boiling, unless you meant 15 seconds.</p>
<p>Anne, you&#8217;re absolutely correct, that macaroni <strong>is</strong> divine, and you can read all about it <a href="http://technically.us/eat/articles/2006/04/15/ruth-reichs-macaroni-and-cheese">here</a>.</p></div>
